# WHAT IT IS
#   gopeaks is the **production CUT&TAG / CUT&RUN peak caller** —
#   the typed bioinformatics workflow:
#
#     1. Wet-lab researcher performs typed CUT&TAG (typed
#        tagmentation-based) or typed CUT&RUN (typed MNase-based)
#        typed experiment with a typed antibody targeting a
#        typed transcription factor (typed FOXA1, CTCF, GATA1,
#        ESR1, MYC, etc.) or typed histone modification (typed
#        H3K4me3 for typed active promoters, typed H3K27me3 for
#        typed Polycomb-repressed regions, typed H3K27ac for
#        typed active enhancers, typed H3K4me1 for typed primed
#        enhancers, typed H3K36me3 for typed gene bodies, typed
#        H3K9me3 for typed heterochromatin)
#     2. Sequencing facility produces typed paired-end Illumina
#        FASTQ reads
#     3. Bioinformatician aligns reads (typed bowtie2 / typed bwa-
#        mem) to typed reference genome producing typed paired-
#        end BAM (typed `--bam treatment.bam`)
#     4. Optional: aligns matched typed IgG / typed input control
#        BAM (`--control igg.bam`)
#     5. gopeaks bins the typed genome into typed sliding windows
#        (default typed `--step 100` bp + `--slide 50` bp; typed
#        `--broad` mode auto-switches to typed 5000/1000 bp for
#        typed H3K27me3 / H3K4me1 / H3K27ac typed broad domains)
#     6. gopeaks counts typed read pairs per bin (typed gonetics
#        typed GRanges typed overlap)
#     7. gopeaks normalizes typed treatment to typed control
#        (typed CPM-scaled typed signal subtraction)
#     8. gopeaks fits a typed negative-binomial distribution
#        typed via typed gonum typed `distuv.NegativeBinomial`
#     9. gopeaks computes typed per-bin p-values + applies typed
#        Benjamini-Hochberg typed multiple-hypothesis correction
#        (typed `--pval 0.05`)
#    10. gopeaks merges typed contiguous typed significant bins
#        within typed `--mdist 1000` bp into typed candidate
#        peaks + applies typed `--minreads 15` typed coverage
#        threshold + typed `--minwidth 150` bp typed minimum
#        peak width
#    11. gopeaks writes typed BED-format typed peaks file (typed
#        `<prefix>_peaks.bed`) + typed JSON metrics typed report
#        (typed `<prefix>_gopeaks.json`)
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from `gopeaks.go` akamensky/
#                       argparse declarations;  extracted via raw
#                       fetch of `gopeaks.go`)
#
#   gopeaks [OPTIONS...]
#
#   Required for actual peak calling:
#     -b, --bam <FILE>                input BAM file
#                                     (paired-end reads required)
#
#   Optional:
#     -c, --control <FILE>            control BAM (IgG, Input)
#                                     for normalization
#     -s, --chromsize <FILE>          chromosome sizes (only
#                                     needed if missing from
#                                     BAM header)
#     -m, --mdist <INT>               merge peaks within <mdist>
#                                     bp (default 1000)
#     -r, --minreads <INT>            minimum read pairs per
#                                     candidate bin (default 15)
#     -p, --pval <FLOAT>              significance threshold
#                                     (Benjamini-Hochberg
#                                     corrected; default 0.05)
#     -t, --step <INT>                bin size for coverage bins
#                                     (default 100;
#                                     `--broad` resets to 5000)
#     -l, --slide <INT>               slide size for coverage
#                                     bins (default 50;
#                                     `--broad` resets to 1000)
#     -w, --minwidth <INT>            minimum peak width in bp
#                                     (default 150)
#     -o, --prefix <STRING>           output prefix (default
#                                     `sample`)
#     -v, --version                   print version + exit
#         --broad                     broad-mark mode (typed
#                                     H3K27ac / H3K4me1 /
#                                     H3K27me3 / H3K9me3 / typed
#                                     H3K36me3);  auto-sets
#                                     `--step 5000` + `--slide
#                                     1000`
